  This document describes the usage of runbuild, the Trilinos make utility.
  
  The runbuild utility provides a standard way to build (configure and compile)
  Trilinos source and generate results.  It relies on the runconfigure and
  runmake utilities for its core functionality.  This simplifies the process of
  automating Trilinos testing when combined with other utilities.
  
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
I.  Prerequisites

  In order for the configure utility to work, you must have the following in
  place:
  
    1.  A complete invoke-configure file.
       
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
II.  Execution

  To execute the Trilinos build utility, simply type:
  
    cd /PATH/TO/Trilinos/commonTools/test/utilities/
    perl runbuild --help
            
  Refer to this help output for the most up-to-date information on usage and
  available options.  (You can use "./" instead of "perl " if your system's
  perl interpreter resides at /usr/bin/perl)
  
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
IV.  Build Results File

  The results of the build attempt will be placed in the specified output
  directory and will be named according to the following scheme:
  
    YR-MO-DA_HR.MN.SE-build/
    
  This directory will contain some number of configure and make results files
  generated by runconfigure and runmake.  See README-runconfigure and
  README-runmake for more information.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------